<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/68718060-nancyj"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1625089996i/68718060._UY100_CR38,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/68718060-nancyj">NancyJ</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">You might have actually read the knock-off book with a very similar title. The Atomic City Girls, which is straight up fiction. It&apos;s outrageous to me <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">You might have actually read the knock-off book with a very similar title. The Atomic City Girls, which is straight up fiction. It's outrageous to me that they used this title to mislead people.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
