<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/534385-did-we-care-what-happened-to-any-of-the">Did we care what happened to any of the women in the story?
We we TERRIBLY upset about the institutionalized racism and prejudice?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_534385'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15801668-the-girls-of-atomic-city">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/534385-did-we-care-what-happened-to-any-of-the">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/534385-did-we-care-what-happened-to-any-of-the">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/5885984-ellen-clark"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/5885984-ellen-clark">Ellen Clark</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I believe the answer to the first question is YES, we do care about what happened to the women following the end of World War II. What became of them,<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I believe the answer to the first question is YES, we do care about what happened to the women following the end of World War II. What became of them, how they lived their lives. Regarding the second question, I suggest that, unfortunately, this was a product of the times in which they were living. Would the same thing happen today. I certainly hope not! However, we cannot go back and re-write the history. I think it is important for people to know exactly what transpired, so we do not repeat the same behaviors!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

