<span id="freeTextContainer13180021272958409671">This one was very interesting because this event took place in the county I grew up. My grandmother and aunt were Atomic Girls. I can remember as a child they kept the details of their time working in Oak Ridge very close, with very little talk on the specifics. I remember my grandmother talking about riding the bus from Knoxville (which was her new home because Douglas Dam/TVA had taken her family farm) to her job in Oak Ridge. My aunt thought she was working for Kodak to help develop product f</span>
  <span id="freeText13180021272958409671" style="display:none">This one was very interesting because this event took place in the county I grew up. My grandmother and aunt were Atomic Girls. I can remember as a child they kept the details of their time working in Oak Ridge very close, with very little talk on the specifics. I remember my grandmother talking about riding the bus from Knoxville (which was her new home because Douglas Dam/TVA had taken her family farm) to her job in Oak Ridge. My aunt thought she was working for Kodak to help develop product for film. Unfortunately, they have both passed, I have gotten older and now have questions that I don't have the opportunity to ask. I know more about my grandmother losing her farm to TVA than the time she worked in Oak Ridge. Today when visiting family, I am able to tell my own child this is one of the gates as we enter Oak Ridge and this is the gate we exit headed to "Nana's House." Many of the places I recognize and I am familiar with. The secrets kept are remarkable and seem impossible in our current time. If you are from the area you never say "Oak Ridge" as two words, it sounds more like Ohkridge. If you know, you know.<br /><br />Updated 4/1/21: after speaking with my mom she confirmed both my aunt and my grandmother were still very tight lipped after their time in OR. Her mother talked a lot about the signs posted everywhere and she was responsible for going over “papers” and condensing findings to send to next person. My aunt who thought she was doing something for film was responsible for reading “gages” all day. Again, very vague details. But it shows they were “Rule followers”</span>
