<div id="review_771533757" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/771533757" />
    <a title="Donna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13244359-donna"><img alt="Donna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396758075p2/13244359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/771533757?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna" href="/user/show/13244359-donna">Donna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13244359-donna?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13244359-donna?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer771533757" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13624163618827555290"><br/>Content: 5 stars<br/><br/>Execution: 3 stars<br/><br/>This is a great story of some of the women who helped with the making of the first atomic bomb. It was fascinating how they were recruited and then carried out their jobs. I loved reading about the history here. I just wasn&apos;t crazy about the writing. Some of it was kind of dry and weighty. Before it even really got started, I thought I wasn&apos;t going to be able to do it.....but I&apos;m glad I did. The story was worth the read.</span>
  <span id="freeText13624163618827555290" style="display:none"><br />Content: 5 stars<br /><br />Execution: 3 stars<br /><br />This is a great story of some of the women who helped with the making of the first atomic bomb. It was fascinating how they were recruited and then carried out their jobs. I loved reading about the history here. I just wasn't crazy about the writing. Some of it was kind of dry and weighty. Before it even really got started, I thought I wasn't going to be able to do it.....but I'm glad I did. The story was worth the read.</span>
