  <span id="freeText4605355764417666970" style="display:none">From the author: "The challenge in telling the story of the atomic bomb is one of nuance, requiring thought and sensitivity and walking a line between commemoration and celebration."<br /><br />I think Kiernan pulls off this difficult high wire act with intelligence, thorough research, personal and homey anecdotes sprinkled with journalistic vignettes on the bomb as it progresses. A close examination of the secret city built in Tennessee, which drafted thousands of female volunteers. An important, though grim, part of our history.</span>
