        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer963880732" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12009296937906833205">I made it to page 111 in chapter 5 and I&apos;m calling it quits. <br/><br/>The construction of this book is lousy. It jumps all over the place, there are too many characters to remember, none of them are memorable, the author relates WAY too much information about the specifics of making the bomb and only provides mundane snippets of the lives of the &quot;girls&quot; and I AM BORED TO TEARS!<br/><br/>Read with SBC book club November 2016 (or not, as the case may be)</span>
  <span id="freeText12009296937906833205" style="display:none">I made it to page 111 in chapter 5 and I'm calling it quits. <br /><br />The construction of this book is lousy. It jumps all over the place, there are too many characters to remember, none of them are memorable, the author relates WAY too much information about the specifics of making the bomb and only provides mundane snippets of the lives of the "girls" and I AM BORED TO TEARS!<br /><br />Read with SBC book club November 2016 (or not, as the case may be)</span>
